HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1575
By Sparks
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Ryan Dudney, 2026
Salutatorian of Smyrna High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those Tennessee students who, through their natural abilities and unwavering pursuit
of academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Ryan Dudney is one such individual, who has been named Salutatorian of
the 2026 graduating class at Smyrna High School; and
WHEREAS, through dedication to her studies, careful recollection of vast amounts of
data, composure through her examinations, and steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms.
Dudney has achieved a remarkable academic feat and joined the ranks of the brightest and
most notable students in the State of Tennessee and the nation; and
WHEREAS, in her educational career, Ms. Dudney has maintained an exemplary grade
point average while participating in a number of extracurricular clubs and activities, including
Smyrna High School volleyball and flag football, Beta Club, Student Council, National Honor
Society, and FCCLA; and
WHEREAS, she has also served as a profession intern teacher at Smyrna High School,
assistant youth flag football coach, and volunteer with the Rocky Fork Elementary School
Library; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Dudney has earned several prestigious awards and accolades,
including honors from the Governor's School for Prospective Teachers, the Smyrna High School
Honors Biology Award, and the Smyrna High School Advanced Placement English Language
and Composition Award; and
HJR1575
018484
- 1 -

WHEREAS, her intellectual aptitude and ambition most certainly bode well for her future
endeavors; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Dudney's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her parents, James and Kari Dudney; her brother, Grant; her school; and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Dudney's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Ryan Dudney of Smyrna High School on being
named the 2026 Salutatorian, salute her impressive academic achievement, and extend to her
our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
